  "prompt": "How can I delete a Google account from my phone?",
  "response": "To delete a Google account from your Android phone, here's a step-by-step guide:\n\n1. **Open Settings**: Tap the gear-shaped Settings icon on your home screen or app drawer.\n\n2. **Accounts**:\n   - Scroll down and select \"Accounts\" or \"Users & accounts.\" The exact wording may vary depending on your device.\n\n3. **Select the Account**:\n   - Find and tap on the Google account you want to remove.\n\n4. **Remove Account**:\n   - Tap on \"Remove account.\" If you're removing the only account on the device and you might want to keep the data, make sure it's backed up.\n   - Confirm your choice by tapping \"Remove account\" again if prompted.\n\nThe account will be removed from your device. This action does not delete the Google account itself; it only removes it from your phone. \n\n**Note**: If you are using an iPhone, the steps are a bit different:\n\n1. **Open Settings**: Tap the Settings icon to open it.\n\n2. **Mail, Contacts, Calendars**:\n   - Scroll down to find \"Mail\" or \"Passwords & Accounts\" based on your iOS version.\n\n3. **Select the Account**:\n   - Tap on the Google account you want to delete.\n\n4. **Delete Account**:\n   - Tap \"Delete Account\" at the bottom of the screen.\n   - Confirm the deletion if prompted.\n\nAgain, this removes the Google account from your device but does not delete the account itself.",
